Create, update, and delete persist the in-flight
OCI work request in `status.async.current`,
normalize AI Language `OperationStatus*` values
into shared async classes, and normalize
work-request `OperationType*` values into
create/update/delete phases before deriving
conditions and requeue.
Create recovers the Project OCID from the create
response when OCI returns it or from
work-request resources when the response omits
it, then polls `GetProject` until the Project
becomes readable. Update also gates completion
on a succeeded work request plus a readable
`GetProject`. Retryable 409 "currently being
modified" conflicts project a lifecycle-sourced
pending update when OCI omits a work-request ID;
later reconciles reread `GetProject`, clear
async if mutable drift is already gone, and
otherwise back off for one normal requeue
interval before retrying `UpdateProject` instead
of hot-looping on every `ACTIVE` reread.
Pre-create lookup adopts only a unique paginated
non-`DELETED` `ListProjects` match on
`compartmentId` and `displayName`. Delete
fallback reuses `status.compartmentId`,
`status.displayName`, and tracked `projectId`
when `GetProject` returns NotFound so finalizer
release does not depend on stale spec values.
Only `displayName`, `description`,
`freeformTags`, and `definedTags` reconcile in
place. `compartmentId` remains replacement-only
drift, so the live runtime never exercises
provider-only `ChangeProjectCompartment`, and
the runtime has no secret side effects.
Delete is not best-effort. The finalizer stays
until the delete work request is terminal and
`GetProject` or fallback `ListProjects` confirms
the Project is gone or exposes lifecycle state
`DELETED`.
end note
